[[File:His Holiness Sri Sri Bhagavan- the founder and core of International Vedanta Society.jpg|thumb|His Holiness Sri Sri Bhagavan - the founder and the core of the International Vedanta Society]] The '''International Vedanta Society''' (or '''IVS''') is a religious organization in India focused on [[Advaita Vedanta]]. <ref>{{cite news |title=Lessons on Vedanta |publisher=Times of India - Kolkata |date=2012-07-02 |accessdate=2012-10-08 |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-07-02/kolkata/32507582_1_rich-tributes-films-shashi-kapoor/2}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Speech on Vedanta by Swami Probuddhananda |publisher=Tilburg University, The Netherlands |date=2011-10-10 |accessdate=2012-10-08 |url=http://www.tilburguniversity.edu/about-tilburg-university/culture-and-sports/academic-forum/academicflashback/swami}}</ref> It is based in [[Birati]], [[West Bengal]], [[India]], and was founded in 1989 by Sri Bhagavan (born 3 January 1942).<ref>{{cite journal |title=A Tribute to Bhagavan |journal=Namarupa, United States |issue=14 |volume=3 |date=2011-09-01 |accessdate=2012-10-08 |author=Alexis Houston Maurya |url=http://www.namarupa.org/volumes/1403.php}}</ref>
