'''Jesús Ramón Martínez de Ezquerecocha Suso''' (31 August 1935 − 16 February 2013) was a [[Spanish people|Spanish]]-born [[Ecuadorian people|Ecuadorian]] [[Roman Catholic]] bishop.

Born in [[Spain]] and ordained to the priesthood on 9 August 1959, Martínez de Ezquerecocha Suso was named bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Babahoyo]], [[Ecuador]] on 28 June 1984 and resigned on 27 March 2008.<ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bmares.html Jesús Ramón Martínez de Ezquerecocha Suso]</ref>

